
Privacy Policy

Last Updated: May 22, 2026

Thank you for using "SnapClip" (hereinafter referred to as "the App"). We take your privacy seriously. This Privacy Policy explains how the App handles your data.

1. Data Collection
The App does not collect any personal information. We:

Do not require account registration

Do not collect your name, email, location, or any other identifying information

Do not integrate any third-party analytics or advertising SDKs

Do not access the internet (the App operates completely offline)

2. Camera & Photo Library Permissions
The App requires access to your camera and photo library solely for document scanning and importing. All captured or imported images are stored exclusively on your device locally. We cannot access, view, or upload them.

3. Document & Image Storage
Your scans, original images, thumbnails, and other files are all stored locally in your device's sandbox (Documents/Scans/ directory). The App has no network permissions and will never transmit any files to external servers. You may delete data within the App at any time, or clear all files through system settings.

4. Third-Party Services
The App does not integrate any third-party services (including but not limited to analytics, crash reporting, advertising, or social sharing SDKs). All features are implemented using Apple's native frameworks, and no information is disclosed to any third party.

5. Children's Privacy
The App does not collect personal data from anyone, including children. If you are a guardian and have questions about data, please contact us using the information below.

6. Policy Changes
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The updated version will be published within the App or on the App Store product page, with the effective date noted. Continued use of the App constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.

